para_trans: Forest Land-Raigad
Diversion of 0.0765 ha. Reserve Forest land

under Van (Sanrakshan Evam Sanvardhan) Adhiniyam, 1980 in favour of M/s. Bharti Airtel Ltd., Pune for laying of underground Optical Fiber Cable along the Road in RoW of NH-66 from Panvel to Pen Road in Raigad District in the State of Maharashtra.
Government of Maharashtra
Revenue and Forest Department
Government Corrigendum No.: FLD- 1324/CR.36/F-10
Mantralaya, Mumbai-400 032
Reference:
Revenue and Forest Department, Government of Maharashtra Order No. FLD-
Corrigendum:-
It has been come to notice that, Sr. No. 5 (a) of 3rd paragraph, in the Govt.
Resolution, referred above, contains some minor mistakes. Therefore, this paragraph should
be read as under:-
3. 5) Net Present Value:-
a) The Forest Department shall charge the Net Present Value (NPV) for the 0.0765 ha.
Forest land to be diverted under this proposal from the User Agency as per the
orders of the Hon'ble Supreme Court of India dated 30/10/2002, 01/08/2003,
as per the guidelines issued by the Ministry vide letters No.5-1/1998-FC (Pt.ID,
dated 18/09/2003 as well as letter No.5-2/2006-FC, dated 03/10/2006 and 5-3/2007-
FC, dated 05/02/2009 & File No.5-3/2011-FC(Vol-I), Dated 06/01/2022 in this
regard.
This Government Corrigendum is available at the Government of Maharashtra's
website www.maharashtra.gov.in with reference No. 202404221755055619 This
